<subSubSection id="2DF0ACA1FFFFFFCFFF71F84CFBC8FF57" lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="25" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="description">
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFFFFFC0FF71F84CFE7DF816" blockId="23.[151,1437,1913,2013]" box="[151,384,1950,1977]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
(
<figureCitation id="FDD1E3AFFFFFFFC0FF79F84CFF14F817" box="[159,233,1950,1977]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="60.[151,250,1932,1956]" captionText="FIGURE 7. Neotropical Eudocima and Ferenta adults (dorsal aspect)." pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Figs 7</figureCitation>
: C–D, 90: G)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFFFFFCFFF71F810FBC8FF57" blockId="23.[151,1437,1913,2013]" lastBlockId="24.[151,1436,151,249]" lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="25" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
This species is separated from other 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFFFFC0FDCAF811FD2AF872" box="[556,727,1986,2013]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Ferenta species</taxonomicName>
by its wider, more ovuloid orange hindwing band. It has a more southern distribution than other 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFF0FFCFFE19FF45FDAAFF1F" box="[511,599,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Ferenta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Ferenta</taxonomicName>
. The 
<typeStatus id="BA514188FFF0FFCFFD75FF45FD3EFF1F" box="[659,707,151,177]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">type</typeStatus>
locality is 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFF0FFCFFCD8FF45FC7FFF1F" box="[830,898,151,177]" name="Brazil" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and all specimens and images we have seen are from southeastern 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFF0FFCFFE8EFF69FE52FF7B" box="[360,431,187,213]" name="Brazil" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, with records extending as far south as 
<collectingRegion id="A72E31C8FFF0FFCFFC8AFF69FBBFFF7B" box="[876,1090,187,213]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
. There are recent photographs, but we are not aware of recent specimens and no COI 5’ sequences were available.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
